SIMPLE: albumen
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Albumen
<hw>Al*bu"men</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>albus</ets> white.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The white of an
egg.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Nourishing matter stored up within
the integuments of the seed in many plants, but not incorporated in the
embryo. It is the floury part in corn, wheat, and like grains, the oily
part in poppy seeds, the fleshy part in the cocoanut, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Albumin</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Albumenize</ent>⟦br⟧
